node.text:
Penggunaan masker pada masa pandemi saat ini sangatlah penting. Selain sebagai alat pelindung diri masker juga menunjukkan kepedulian kita terhadap orang lain untuk meminimalisir penyebaran Covid-19. Disituasi saat ini dengan adanya kewajiban untuk memakai masker muncul ide kreatif dari sosok ibu persit. Ide kreatif ini bisa dikatakan untuk mengatasi pembatasan ruang gerak masyarakat dan bisa menjadikan peluang bisnis. Beliau adalah Ibu Nor Puji Astuti, kreativitas pembuatan masker kain yang beliau lakukan dapat kita lihat melalui video ini, semoga bermanfaat?

node.text:
El método por vía seca es también conocido como PROCESO NATURAL?
Es tal vez el mas antiguo y requiere poca maquinaria, aunque mas labor. El método consiste en secar la cereza entera despues de haberla recolectado, sin remover la piel o cáscara.

-Dos de los factores mas importantes son: Recolectar la cereza en el punto óptimo de maduración ? y moverlo constantemente durante el secado, para que este sea parejo y evitar la formación de hongos.

- Es el proceso mas amigable con el medio ambiente??

-Nuestro café planadas pasó por este proceso, por lo que se puede distinguir sus notas son exóticas. 
.
.

“Hive #1” The first in a limited series of thirteen pieces, the Hive Series was started in March and is about the quick shift we all made to a strictly online presence. The pandemic has forced us to embrace technology for things we’d normally prefer to do in person. I began to think about all the things I’m doing online and how sometimes it’s really freaking awkward and so then I just don’t do those things anymore. I’m in my house working everyday and struggling to figure out how to connect people to my artwork in a time when art is pure luxury. It’s weird putting all these creations out into the universe and just waiting. The loss of control is maddening. We’re all connected more than ever through technology but yet I’ve never felt more disconnected from people in my life. The irony is staggering.

How was Tali ever this small!??⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We get asked all the time where we got Tali from, she was yellow girl in her litter from @rockyroaddoodles in Utah. Her dog parents were Blaze and Zelda. ⁣

I flew out to pick her up last minute because the flight nanny agency couldn’t find someone to fly her out to us that whole week. I woke up at 5am and told my husband as soon as he woke up “I want to fly to Utah to go get our puppy!” Pretty sure he only agreed because he’s gotten quite used to my crazy dog mom ways.?⁣
